    "Here, 0.2% of the instances are responsible for half of the total running time.",
    "The difference in average running time for the same threshold can likely be attributed to a difference in ILP solver settings, see the Methods section for details.",
    "We did not use a running time limit for the ILP solver, see Methods section.",
    "Finally, we analyzed the error of computing bounds instead of exact distances: The myopic MCES distance may differ from the exact distance; the absolute error is the difference between the exact distance value and the myopic MCES distance.",
    "Recall that the myopic MCES distance is a lower bound, so the absolute error is never negative."
